    <p align="left"><b><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#004080">Submarine
    Officer Assignments Exceptional Customer Service</font></b></p>
    <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Arial"><img border="0" src="/web/20060928003851im_/http://www.chinfo.navy.mil/navpalib/cno/n87/usw/issue_8/downlin6.gif" align="left" hspace="5" width="118" height="108">In
    December 1999 Rear Admiral J.B. Hinkle (COMNAVPERSCOM) established the
    &quot;Pickle&quot; award to recognize those command personnel who &quot;go
    the extra mile&quot; to provide exceptional customer service. The award is
    based on the philosophy of &quot;Give 'Em the Pickleï¿½and they'll be
    back&quot; advocated by Mr. Robert Farrell, a successful businessman and
    creator of Farrell's Ice Cream Parlors. Mr. Farrell tells a story of a
    business that lost a customer because they wouldn't serve him a pickle with
    his sandwich. He uses the pickle analogy to show that organizations can
    exceed their customer's expectations by going the extra mile for their
    business. The &quot;Pickle&quot; award consists of a &quot;Give 'Em the
    Pickle&quot; mug imprinted with the NAVPERSCOM logo. Above, Admiral Hinkle
    awards LCDR Michael Holland (PERS 421A - Department Head Detailer) the
    &quot;Pickle Award&quot; for March 2000. LCDR Holland has been the Submarine
    Department Head Detailer for nearly two years. He was recognized for his
    outstanding contributions to Junior Officer retention using every detailing
    avenue in efforts to help officers stay Navy while serving their personal
    and professional needs.</font></p>
